column5: Took out a couple on Cedar and 2 muskies hit the bag.Had quite a few sightings but not many where aggressive but maybe the cold front has them slowed down.Weather hasnt been great,very windy everyday butcdudcgetca bunch ofcsome much needed rain.Anyways will use that as a excuse for slower muskie fishing.Were by the pipes from Clifff into Cedar and barely a trickle coming through there.Check out that pic.Havntvseen rocks like that there for years.
